headline.main: Some Pages From an Old Congressional Record

lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON, Oct. 16 -- History is not in the least likely to repeat itself in the consideration of the armed ship bill by the present Congress. Even if opposing Senators should attempt the filibuster they have abjured in advance, the present bill cannot be ''killed by the Constitution" as its ancestor was in 1917.
abstract: Krock on why opponents cannot kill bill by filibuster
